					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-subjectpageheader">
</div><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Mathematical function having a characteristic S-shaped curve or sigmoid curve</div>  
<p class="mw-empty-elt"> 
  
</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Logistic-curve.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Logistic-curve.svg/250px-Logistic-curve.svg.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="167" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Logistic-curve.svg/500px-Logistic-curve.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="400" /></a><figcaption>The <a href="/wiki/Logistic_curve" class="mw-redirect" title="Logistic curve">logistic curve</a></figcaption></figure>  
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Error_Function.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Error_Function.svg/250px-Error_Function.svg.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="175" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Error_Function.svg/500px-Error_Function.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="420" /></a><figcaption>Plot of the <a href="/wiki/Error_function" title="Error function">error function</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>A <b>sigmoid function</b> is any <a href="/wiki/Mathematical_function" class="mw-redirect" title="Mathematical function">mathematical function</a> whose <a href="/wiki/Graph_of_a_function" title="Graph of a function">graph</a> has a characteristic S-shaped or <b>sigmoid curve</b>.
</p><p>A common example of a sigmoid function is the <a href="/wiki/Logistic_function" title="Logistic function">logistic function</a>, which is defined by the formula<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Han-Morag&#95;1995&#95;1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Han-Morag_1995-1"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \sigma (x)={\frac {1}{1+e^{-x}}}={\frac {e^{x}}{1+e^{x}}}=1-\sigma (-x).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>&#x03C3;<!-- σ --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <msup>
                <mi>e</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>
                  <mi>x</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <msup>
              <mi>e</mi>
